{
  "texts": [
    "For example, LATTICE [250] is a digital twin-based anomaly detection method employing deep curriculum learning.",
    "It assigns difficulty scores to each sample and uses a training scheduler to sample batches of training data based on these scores, facilitating learning from easy to difficult data.",
    "This approach has shown to be more effective than their previous DL-based proposal, ATTAIN [249].",
    "LATTICE was evaluated on multiple CPS benchmarks including Secure Water Treatment (SWaT) [138], Water Distribution (WADI) [4], Battle of Attack Detection Algorithms (BATADAL) [216], Gas Pipeline Dataset [152].",
    "Additionally, Xu et al. [251] identified challenges related to data complexity and insufficiency within CPS, particularly in train control and management systems."
  ]
}